January 30, 1919.

Old Broadway (formerly Bloomingdale Road), north from W. 126th (formerly Lawrence) Street, showing this old thoroughfare curving westward in its northward trek. To the right (in view No. 1) is a three story unit of the Sheltering Arms and occupies the S.E. corner of W. 129th Street. View No. 2 shows only the buildings at the N.E. corner. They are numbered 29-31-33 Old Broadway; The latter two are of frame construction.

April 1, 1938.
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr
